OL,3,COfficer accused of Kaba murder thought
OL,4,Ccolleague was 'about to die', court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FHe told the court that prior to the
OL,8,Fshooting he'd never fired a gun at a
OL,9,Freal human being or seen a colleague
OL,10,Ffire a gun at a real human being.
OL,12,FHe added he did not intend to kill, as
OL,13,Fthe training he received is to fire to
OL,14,Fincapacitate. He said he fired because
OL,15,Fhe wanted Chris Kaba's vehicle to
OL,16,Fstop, and that he wasn't angry,
OL,17,Ffrustrated or annoyed before during or
OL,18,Fafter he fired shots.
